      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "JUST A JOURNEY (3) has not raced for eight months but looks forward enough for the return after two recent trials, winning the latest. Maiden winner at Melton when last seen and as that was just her second start she has upside. Should enjoy a nice run from this favourable starting position. Expecting a bright start to the campaign. BUTLERS WHARF (8) was better behaved at his second start and showed some ability when he scored by 7.6 metres at this venue. Can settle just behind them and wait on the sprint lane. Could go through his grades now. WOMAN TO LOVE (1) drew wider and raced parked but fought well to miss narrowly as runner-up on debut at Kilmore. This looks stronger but she gets the ace draw and is open to natural improvement. SAMMY HALLER (6) has come from the back row for fourth at his last two appearances and his lone win came at this distance.",
